panda.dao.sql.executor

Class DynamicSqlExecutor

  • java.lang.Object
    • panda.dao.sql.executor.JdbcSqlExecutor
      • panda.dao.sql.executor.SimpleSqlExecutor
        • panda.dao.sql.executor.DynamicSqlExecutor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SqlExecutor

    public class DynamicSqlExecutor
extends SimpleSqlExecutor
    SqlExecutor supports dynamic sql. 
     Dynamic SQL: 
    @ --> (at mark) at something
    @!  --> not at something
 
    1) SELECT * FROM SAMPLE
         @[ WHERE
           @[(@id[ID=:id] @name[OR NAME=:name] @bool[OR BOOL=:bool])]
           @list[AND LIST IN (:list)]
           @kind[AND KIND=:kind]
           @!kind[AND KIND IS NULL]
         ]
         @orderCol[ ORDER BY ::orderCol ::orderDir ]
 
    descripton:
      @id[ID=:id] --> append sql when id is not null
      @bool[BOOL=:bool] --> append sql when bool is TRUE
      @list[LIST IN (:list)]  --> append sql when list != null && list.size() > 0 (:list --> ?, ?, ?)
      @[ WHERE ... ]  --> append sql when all the logical expression in @[...] is true
      @!kind[AND KIND IS NULL] --> append sql when kind is null
 
    2) UPDATE SAMPLE
         SET
           @name[,NAME=:name]
           @kind[,KIND=:kind]
           ,OTHER='@kind[,KIND=:kind]'
         WHERE
           ID=:id
